    • Constructor Detail

      • QoS

        @Since(value="7.0")
public QoS(Optional<Long> minIOPS,
              Optional<Long> maxIOPS,
              Optional<Long> burstIOPS,
              Optional<Long> burstTime)
        Quality of Service (QoS) values are used on SolidFire volumes to provision performance expectations. Minimum, maximum and burst QoS values can be set within the ranges specified in the QoS table below.

        Volumes created without specified QoS values are created with the Default values listed below. Default values can be found by running the GetDefaultQoS method.

        NameMin Allowed
        (v7.0/v8.0)        		DefaultMax Allowed
        minIOPS100/5010015,000
        maxIOPS100/5015,000100,000
        burstIOPS100/5015,000100,000
        Parameters:
        minIOPS - (optional) Desired minimum 4KB IOPS to guarantee.
        maxIOPS - (optional) Desired maximum 4KB IOPS allowed over an extended period of time.
        burstIOPS - (optional) Maximum "peak" 4KB IOPS allowed for short periods of time.
        burstTime - (optional) The length of time burstIOPS is allowed.
        Since:
        7.0

    • Method Detail

      • getMinIOPS

        public Optional<Long> getMinIOPS()
        Desired minimum 4KB IOPS to guarantee. The allowed IOPS will only drop below this level if all volumes have been capped at their minIOPS value and there is still insufficient performance capacity.

      • getMaxIOPS

        public Optional<Long> getMaxIOPS()
        Desired maximum 4KB IOPS allowed over an extended period of time.

      • getBurstIOPS

        public Optional<Long> getBurstIOPS()
        Maximum "peak" 4KB IOPS allowed for short periods of time. Allows for bursts of I/O activity over the normal maxIOPS value.

      • getBurstTime

        public Optional<Long> getBurstTime()
        The length of time burstIOPS is allowed. The value returned is represented in time units of seconds.
        NOTE: this value is calculated by the system based on IOPS set for QoS.
